===Noun===
'''vector'''

#(''Mathematics'') a [[quantity]] that has both [[magnitude]] and [[direction]], typically written as a column of [[number]]s (or, occasionally, as a row of scalars) enclosed in [[parentheses]].  Compare [[scalar]]
# a chosen course or direction for motion, as of an aircraft.

====Translations====

*[[French]]: [[vecteur]] ''m''
*[[Italian]]: [[vettore]] ''m''
*[[Slovenian]]: [[vektor]] ''m''

===Verb===
'''to vector'''

# to set a course of motion in a particular direction, especially with intention to reach a selected end point.